Taranaki method
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a basic method of making silage where a hole is dug and the silage buried.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  17/10/1903
Source:  Farmers' Advocate
Author:
Vol / Page:  5
Edition:
Quote:  The 'Taranaki method' of ensilage stacking - stacking grass, green oats or anything handy, and weighing it by earth excavated from the side of the stack, the earth being afterwards replaced when the silage was being used. The Taranaki method should become popular among New Zealand dairymen.
